globalCheckStaticDepends.name: globalCheckStaticDepends
globalCheckStaticDepends.description: Indicates whether the availability of virtual servers on load-balancing routers and hosts is checked. Normally true, but can be false for testing.

globalTimerGetLBRouterData.name: globalTimerGetLBRouterData
globalTimerGetLBRouterData.description: Interval in seconds between refreshes of load-balancing router data.

globalTimerGetVServData.name: globalTimerGetVServData
globalTimerGetVServData.description: Interval in seconds between refreshes of virtual server data.

globalTimerGetPathData.name: globalTimerGetPathData
globalTimerGetPathData.description: Interval in seconds between refreshes of path data.

globalLBRouterTTL.name: globalLBRouterTTL
globalLBRouterTTL.description: Amount of time in seconds that load-balancing router data is considered valid for name resolution and load balancing.

globalVSTTL.name: globalVSTTL
globalVSTTL.description: Amount of time in seconds that virtual server data is considered valid for name resolution and load balancing.

globalPathTTL.name: globalPathTTL
globalPathTTL.description: Amount of time in seconds that path data is considered valid for name resolution and load balancing.

globalRTTTimeout.name: globalRTTTimeout
globalRTTTimeout.description: Amount of time in seconds that the RTT listener daemon waits for a probe.

globalRTTSampleCount.name: globalRTTSampleCount
globalRTTSampleCount.description: Number of packets to send when measuring round-trip times.

globalRTTPacketLength.name: globalRTTPacketLength
globalRTTPacketLength.description: Length in bytes of packets used for measuring round-trip times.

globalRTTProbeProtocol.name: globalRTTProbeProtocol
globalRTTProbeProtocol.description: Probing protocol used for measuring round-trip times.

globalEncryption.name: globalEncryption
globalEncryption.description: Indicates whether encryption is used for iQuery events.

globalEncryptionKeyFile.name: globalEncryptionKeyFile
globalEncryptionKeyFile.description: The pathname of the key file used for encryption.

globalPathHiWater.name: globalPathHiWater
globalPathHiWater.description: Path memory usage level that triggers reaping, in bytes.

globalPathLoWater.name: globalPathLoWater
globalPathLoWater.description: Path memory usage level at which reaping is discontinued, in bytes.

globalPathDuration.name: globalPathDuration
globalPathDuration.description: Interval in seconds between checks of path memory usage to determine whether to reap.

globalPathReapAlg.name: globalPathReapAlg
globalPathReapAlg.description: Algorithm used for selecting paths to be discarded when reaping.

globalTimerKeepAlive.name: globalTimerKeepAlive
globalTimerKeepAlive.description: Interval in seconds between periodic queries of load-balancing routers.

globalRxBufSize.name: globalRxBufSize
globalRxBufSize.description: Size of each socket receive buffer, in bytes.

globalTxBufSize.name: globalTxBufSize
globalTxBufSize.description: Size of each socket transmit buffer, in bytes.

globalQosCoeffRTT.name: globalQosCoeffRTT
globalQosCoeffRTT.description: Relative weight given to the round-trip time in the quality of service load balancing mode.

globalQosCoeffCompletionRate.name: globalQosCoeffCompletionRate
globalQosCoeffCompletionRate.description: Relative weight given to the completion rate in the quality of service load balancing mode.

globalQosCoeffHops.name: globalQosCoeffHops
globalQosCoeffHops.description: Relative weight given to the hop count in the quality of service load balancing mode.

globalQosCoeffPacketRate.name: globalQosCoeffPacketRate
globalQosCoeffPacketRate.description: Relative weight given to the packet rate in the quality of service load balancing mode.

globalPathsNoClobber.name: globalPathsNoClobber
globalPathsNoClobber.description: Specifies whether the load-balancing DNS server overwrites existing path data with blank data when a path probe fails.

globalPathsNeverDie.name: globalPathsNeverDie
globalPathsNeverDie.description: Specifies whether dynamic load balancing modes can use path data even after the ttl for the path data has expired.

globalRegulateInit.name: globalRegulateInit
globalRegulateInit.description: Defines the initial amount of path probe requests 3DNS will send to each big3d after initialization. After the first series of probe requests, 3DNS adjusts the number of future probe requests according to the amount received during the last probe interval (defined by timer_get_path_data) plus the increment defined by regulate_paths.

globalRegulatePaths.name: globalRegulatePaths
globalRegulatePaths.description: If zero, no path regulation will be attempted. Every path in the cache that is not fresh will be sent to each big3d every timer_get_path_data seconds. If non-zero, this defines the increment over the amount of path's probed and refreshed over the past interval to determine an upper bound for probe requests to send to each big3d.

globalProberAddr.name: globalProberAddr
globalProberAddr.description: The default prober for host status.

globalCheckDynamicDepends.name: globalCheckDynamicDepends
globalCheckDynamicDepends.description: Indicates whether the load-balancing DNS server checks the availability of a path before it uses the path for load balancing.

globalDefaultFallback.name: globalDefaultFallback
globalDefaultFallback.description: The default load balancing mode used for the fallback method.

globalDefaultTTL.name: globalDefaultTTL
globalDefaultTTL.description: The amount of time (in seconds) that information is to be used for name resolution and load balancing.

globalPersistLDns.name: globalPersistLDns
globalPersistLDns.description: If TRUE (default), then 3DNS will remember all LDNS's that make requests in its cache. This must be TRUE in order to store and use path information.

globalFbRespectAcl.name: globalFbRespectAcl
globalFbRespectAcl.description: Indicates whether the load-balancing DNS server imposes access control when load balancing switches to the specified fallback mode.

globalFbRespectDepends.name: globalFbRespectDepends
globalFbRespectDepends.description: Indicates whether the load-balancing DNS server respects virtual server status when load balancing switches to the specified fallback mode.

globalHostTTL.name: globalHostTTL
globalHostTTL.description: The amount of time (in seconds) that host machine information is to be used for name resolution and load balancing.

globalTimerGetHostData.name: globalTimerGetHostData
globalTimerGetHostData.description: The interval (in seconds) between refreshes of host information.

globalRTTRetireZero.name: globalRTTRetireZero
globalRTTRetireZero.description: Default 0. Coefficient used in custom path prioritization algorithm.

globalRTTPortDiscovery.name: globalRTTPortDiscovery
globalRTTPortDiscovery.description: Indicates whether the load-balancing DNS server uses the discovery factory to find an alternate port to be used by the probing factory, if probing on port 53 fails.

globalRTTDiscoveryMethod.name: globalRTTDiscoveryMethod
globalRTTDiscoveryMethod.description: Indicates the set of ports scanned when searching for an alternate port to be used bythe probing factory, if probing on port 53 fails.

globalRTTProbeDynamic.name: globalRTTProbeDynamic
globalRTTProbeDynamic.description: Indicates whether the load-balancing DNS server attempts a second probe using the alternate probe protocol if the probe protocol specified by globalRTTProbeProtocol fails during the first probe.

globalCoeffLastAccess.name: globalCoeffLastAccess
globalCoeffLastAccess.description: Default 0. Coefficient used in custom path prioritization algorithm.

globalCoeffFreshRemain.name: globalCoeffFreshRemain
globalCoeffFreshRemain.description: Default 0. Coefficient used in custom path prioritization algorithm.

globalCoeffAccessRefresh.name: globalCoeffAccessRefresh
globalCoeffAccessRefresh.description: Default 0. Coefficient used in custom path prioritization algorithm.

globalCoeffAccessTotal.name: globalCoeffAccessTotal
globalCoeffAccessTotal.description: Default 0. Coefficient used in custom path prioritization algorithm.

globalCoeffDRTT.name: globalCoeffDRTT
globalCoeffDRTT.description: Relative weighting for round trip time when the load balancing mode is set to Quality of Service.

globalCoeffDCompletionRate.name: globalCoeffDCompletionRate
globalCoeffDCompletionRate.description: Default 0. Coefficient used in custom path prioritization algorithm.

globalQosCoeffTopology.name: globalQosCoeffTopology
globalQosCoeffTopology.description: Relative weighting for topology when the load balancing mode is set to Quality of Service.

globalQosFactorRTT.name: globalQosFactorRTT
globalQosFactorRTT.description: Factor used to normalize raw RTT values when computing the QOS score.

globalQosFactorHops.name: globalQosFactorHops
globalQosFactorHops.description: Factor used to normalize raw RTT values when computing the QOS score.

globalQosFactorCompletionRate.name: globalQosFactorCompletionRate
globalQosFactorCompletionRate.description: Factor used to normalize raw RTT values when computing the QOS score.

globalQosFactorPacketRate.name: globalQosFactorPacketRate
globalQosFactorPacketRate.description: Factor used to normalize raw RTT values when computing the QOS score.

globalQosFactorTopology.name: globalQosFactorTopology
globalQosFactorTopology.description: Factor used to normalize raw RTT values when computing the QOS score.

globalLDnsHiWater.name: globalLDnsHiWater
globalLDnsHiWater.description: LDNS memory usage level that triggers reaping, in bytes.

globalLDnsLoWater.name: globalLDnsLoWater
globalLDnsLoWater.description: LDNS memory usage level at which reaping is discontinued, in bytes.

globalLDnsDuration.name: globalLDnsDuration
globalLDnsDuration.description: Interval in seconds between checks of LDNS memory usage to determine whether to reap.

globalLDnsReapAlg.name: globalLDnsReapAlg
globalLDnsReapAlg.description: Algorithm used for selecting LDNS entries to be discarded when reaping.

globalUseAltIqPort.name: globalUseAltIqPort
globalUseAltIqPort.description: If true, the registered port 4353 is used for iQuery traffic. If false, the traditional port 245 is used.

globalMultiplexIq.name: globalMultiplexIq
globalMultiplexIq.description: If true, port 4353 is used for all incoming iQuery traffic. If false, ports from the ephemeral port range are used.

globalRTTProbeProtocolList.name: globalRTTProbeProtocolList
globalRTTProbeProtocolList.description: List of RTT probe protocols to use. The protocols are listed in the order in which they will be attempted. If an attempt to use a specified protocol fails, the next one in the list will be used for a subsequent attempt. If the last protocol in the list fails the first one in the list will then be used.

globalRTTProbeProtocolState.name: globalRTTProbeProtocolState
globalRTTProbeProtocolState.description: The current RTT probe protocol being used. This will return the name of the protocol being used followed by a number signifying the position of that protocol in the list of protocols returned by globalRTTProbeProtocolList.

globalResetCounters.name: globalResetCounters
globalResetCounters.description: Writing a one to this variable will cause counters within 3DNS to be reset. If the counters have been reset this variable will have a value of 1. If the counters have not been reset the variable will have a value of 2.

globalResetCounterTime.name: globalResetCounterTime
globalResetCounterTime.description: The time of the last reset of the 3DNS counters. If the counters have not been reset this variable will contain the time when statistic gathering first started.

dataCenterTable.name: dataCenterTable
dataCenterTable.description: Information describing the defined data centers.

dataCenterEntry.name: dataCenterEntry
dataCenterEntry.description: This table contains a row for each data center. The rows are indexed by the names of the data centers.

dataCenterName.name: dataCenterName
dataCenterName.description: The name of the data center in this row of the table.

dataCenterContact.name: dataCenterContact
dataCenterContact.description: Contact information for the data center in this row of the table.

dataCenterLocation.name: dataCenterLocation
dataCenterLocation.description: The location of the data center in this row of the table.

dataCenterPathCount.name: dataCenterPathCount
dataCenterPathCount.description: The number of paths in the data center in this row of the table.

dataCenterDisabled.name: dataCenterDisabled
dataCenterDisabled.description: Is this datacenter disabled. If a datacenter is disabled then all servers within the datacenter are treated as disabled.

dataCenterDisableDuration.name: dataCenterDisableDuration
dataCenterDisableDuration.description: The duration of a disable of this datacenter.

dataCenterServTable.name: dataCenterServTable
dataCenterServTable.description: Information about the servers associated with each data center.

dataCenterServEntry.name: dataCenterServEntry
dataCenterServEntry.description: This table contains a row for each server in each data center.

dataCenterServAddr.name: dataCenterServAddr
dataCenterServAddr.description: The IP address of the server.

lbRouterTable.name: lbRouterTable
lbRouterTable.description: Information about the defined load-balancing routers.

lbRouterEntry.name: lbRouterEntry
lbRouterEntry.description: This table contains a row for each load-balancing router known to the system. It is indexed by the router's canonical IP address.

lbRouterAddr.name: lbRouterAddr
lbRouterAddr.description: The load-balancing router's canonical IP address.

lbRouterVServCount.name: lbRouterVServCount
lbRouterVServCount.description: The number of virtual servers associated with the load-balancing router.

lbRouterPicks.name: lbRouterPicks
lbRouterPicks.description: The number of times the specified load-balancing router has been chosen by the load-balancing DNS server.

lbRouterRefreshes.name: lbRouterRefreshes
lbRouterRefreshes.description: The number of times that server and connection counts have been refreshed with new data from the load-balancing router.

lbRouterDisabled.name: lbRouterDisabled
lbRouterDisabled.description: Is this load -balancing router disabled. If a load-balancing router is disabled then all of its virtual servers are considered to be disabled.

lbRouterDisableDuration.name: lbRouterDisableDuration
lbRouterDisableDuration.description: Duration of a disable of this load-balancing router.

lbRouterIQProto.name: lbRouterIQProto
lbRouterIQProto.description: IQuery protocol to use for this load-balancing router.

lbRouterIfTable.name: lbRouterIfTable
lbRouterIfTable.description: Information about the network interfaces on a load-balancing router.

lbRouterIfEntry.name: lbRouterIfEntry
lbRouterIfEntry.description: This table contains a row for each network interface associated with a load-balancing router. It is indexed by the canonical IP address of the router and the specific IP address of the interface.

lbRouterIfAddr.name: lbRouterIfAddr
lbRouterIfAddr.description: The specific IP address of the network interface in this row of the table.

lbRouterIfShared.name: lbRouterIfShared
lbRouterIfShared.description: Whether the interface is the shared IP address of the load-balancing router.

lbRouterIfStatus.name: lbRouterIfStatus
lbRouterIfStatus.description: The status of the network interface.

lbRouterIfTXPackets.name: lbRouterIfTXPackets
lbRouterIfTXPackets.description: The number of packets that have been transmitted on the network interface.

lbRouterIfRXPackets.name: lbRouterIfRXPackets
lbRouterIfRXPackets.description: The number of packets that have been received on the network interface.

lbRouterIfPacketRate.name: lbRouterIfPacketRate
lbRouterIfPacketRate.description: The interface's current packet rate in packets per second.

lbRouterIfUpTime.name: lbRouterIfUpTime
lbRouterIfUpTime.description: The amount of time the interface has been up.

lbRouterIfAliveTime.name: lbRouterIfAliveTime
lbRouterIfAliveTime.description: The most recent date and time when the interface was known to be running.

lbRouterIfDataTime.name: lbRouterIfDataTime
lbRouterIfDataTime.description: The most recent date and time when data was transmitted through the interface.

lbRouterIfPathSentTime.name: lbRouterIfPathSentTime
lbRouterIfPathSentTime.description: The date and time when path data corresponding to the interface was most recently sent.

lbRouterIfPathsSent.name: lbRouterIfPathsSent
lbRouterIfPathsSent.description: The number of paths sent in the most recent batch.

lbRouterIfPathsRcvd.name: lbRouterIfPathsRcvd
lbRouterIfPathsRcvd.description: The number of paths received in the most recent batch.

lbRouterIfPathSends.name: lbRouterIfPathSends
lbRouterIfPathSends.description: The number of batches of paths that have been sent.

lbRouterIfPathRcvs.name: lbRouterIfPathRcvs
lbRouterIfPathRcvs.description: The number of batches of paths that have been received.

lbRouterIfAvgPathsSentX1000.name: lbRouterIfAvgPathsSentX1000
lbRouterIfAvgPathsSentX1000.description: The average sent path batch size, multiplied by 1000.

lbRouterIfAvgPathsRcvdX1000.name: lbRouterIfAvgPathsRcvdX1000
lbRouterIfAvgPathsRcvdX1000.description: The average received path batch size, multiplied by 1000.

lbRouterIfFctryTable.name: lbRouterIfFctryTable
lbRouterIfFctryTable.description: Information about the factories running on each load-balancing router interface.

lbRouterIfFctryEntry.name: lbRouterIfFctryEntry
lbRouterIfFctryEntry.description: This table gives the number of factories of each type that are running on each load-balancing router interface.

lbRouterIfFctryType.name: lbRouterIfFctryType
lbRouterIfFctryType.description: The type of the factory in this row of the table.

lbRouterIfFctryCount.name: lbRouterIfFctryCount
lbRouterIfFctryCount.description: The number of factories of the type corresponding to this row of the table.

lbRouterVServTable.name: lbRouterVServTable
lbRouterVServTable.description: Information about the virtual servers associated with each load-balancing router.

lbRouterVServEntry.name: lbRouterVServEntry
lbRouterVServEntry.description: This table contains a row for each virtual server on each load-balancing router. It is indexed by the router address and by the address/port combination that defines the virtual server.

lbRouterVServAddr.name: lbRouterVServAddr
lbRouterVServAddr.description: The IP address of the virtual server.

lbRouterVServPort.name: lbRouterVServPort
lbRouterVServPort.description: The port number of the virtual server.

lbRouterVServXlatedAddr.name: lbRouterVServXlatedAddr
lbRouterVServXlatedAddr.description: The translated (NAT) address of the virtual server.

lbRouterVServXlatedPort.name: lbRouterVServXlatedPort
lbRouterVServXlatedPort.description: The translated (NAT) port number of the virtual server.

lbRouterVServProbeProtocol.name: lbRouterVServProbeProtocol
lbRouterVServProbeProtocol.description: The probing protocol used for measuring round-trip times to the virtual server.

lbRouterVServPicks.name: lbRouterVServPicks
lbRouterVServPicks.description: The number of times the specified virtual server has been chosen by the load-balancing DNS server.

lbRouterVServRefreshes.name: lbRouterVServRefreshes
lbRouterVServRefreshes.description: The number of times that data associated with the virtual server have been refreshed with new information.

lbRouterVServAliveTime.name: lbRouterVServAliveTime
lbRouterVServAliveTime.description: When the virtual server was last known to be up.

lbRouterVServDataTime.name: lbRouterVServDataTime
lbRouterVServDataTime.description: When data was last received from the virtual server.

lbRouterVServCurConns.name: lbRouterVServCurConns
lbRouterVServCurConns.description: The current number of connections being processed by the virtual server.

lbRouterVServCurConnLimit.name: lbRouterVServCurConnLimit
lbRouterVServCurConnLimit.description: The current connection limit for the virtual server.

lbRouterVServCurNodesUp.name: lbRouterVServCurNodesUp
lbRouterVServCurNodesUp.description: The current number of nodes associated with the virtual server that are up.

lbRouterVServCurEnabled.name: lbRouterVServCurEnabled
lbRouterVServCurEnabled.description: Whether the virtual server is currently enabled.

lbRouterVServDnsServDisabled.name: lbRouterVServDnsServDisabled
lbRouterVServDnsServDisabled.description: Whether the virtual server is currently disabled from the load-balancing DNS server.

lbRouterVServDisableDuration.name: lbRouterVServDisableDuration
lbRouterVServDisableDuration.description: Duration of a disable of this server by the load-balancing DNS server.

hostTable.name: hostTable
hostTable.description: Information about the defined hosts other than load-balancing routers.

hostEntry.name: hostEntry
hostEntry.description: This table contains a row for each host other than the load-balancing routers. It is indexed by the canonical IP address of each host.

hostAddr.name: hostAddr
hostAddr.description: The canonical IP address of the host.

hostProber.name: hostProber
hostProber.description: The IP address of the prober for the host.

hostProbeProtocol.name: hostProbeProtocol
hostProbeProtocol.description: The protocol used when probing the host.

hostProbePort.name: hostProbePort
hostProbePort.description: The port to which probes are directed.

hostVServCount.name: hostVServCount
hostVServCount.description: The number of virtual servers associated with the host.

hostStatus.name: hostStatus
hostStatus.description: The current status of the host.

hostPicks.name: hostPicks
hostPicks.description: The number of times the host has been chosen by the load-balancing DNS server.

hostRefreshes.name: hostRefreshes
hostRefreshes.description: The number of times the data from the host has been refreshed with new information.

hostDisabled.name: hostDisabled
hostDisabled.description: Is this load host disabled. If a host is disabled then all of its virtual servers are considered to be disabled.

hostDisableDuration.name: hostDisableDuration
hostDisableDuration.description: Duration of a disable of this host.

hostMetrics.name: hostMetrics
hostMetrics.description: Are Cisco virtual server metrics available for the virtual servers on this host.

hostMemory.name: hostMemory
hostMemory.description: Total number of kilobytes of free virtual memory for this host. If this statistic is not available it will have a value of -1.

hostCPU.name: hostCPU
hostCPU.description: CPU utilization. All CPU utilization is expressed a percentage rounded up to the nearest integer. CPU utilization is computed differently for each SNMP agent. CPU usage is computed for the UCD mib as the load average in the last 5 minutes divided by a configured maximum saturated load average. CPU usage is computed for the Solstice mib as the number of time ticks spent in user and system execution divided by the total number of elapsed time tics. If this statistic is not available it will have a value of -1.

hostDiskSpace.name: hostDiskSpace
hostDiskSpace.description: The amount of available disk space for / in kilobytes. If this statistic is not available it will have a value of -1.

hostSNMPConfigured.name: hostSNMPConfigured
hostSNMPConfigured.description: Is an SNMP agent configured for this host.

hostSNMPAgentType.name: hostSNMPAgentType
hostSNMPAgentType.description: Is an SNMP agent configured for this host.

hostSNMPAddress.name: hostSNMPAddress
hostSNMPAddress.description: The IP address of the SNMP agent for this host. If no SNMP agent is configured for this host this will have a value of 0.0.0.0.

hostSNMPPort.name: hostSNMPPort
hostSNMPPort.description: The port for the SNMP agent of this host. If no SNMP agent is configured for this host this will have a value of -1.

hostSNMPRetries.name: hostSNMPRetries
hostSNMPRetries.description: Number of retries to use when attempting to query the SNMP agent of this host. If no SNMP agent is configured for this host this will have a value of -1.

hostSNMPTimeout.name: hostSNMPTimeout
hostSNMPTimeout.description: Time in seconds to wait before retrying a query of the SNMP agent for this host. If no SNMP agent is configured for this host this will have a value of -1.

hostSNMPVersion.name: hostSNMPVersion
hostSNMPVersion.description: SNMP version number to use when communicating with the SNMP agent for this host. If no SNMP agent is configured for this host this will have a value of -1.

hostSNMPCommunity.name: hostSNMPCommunity
hostSNMPCommunity.description: SNMP community name to use when communicating with the SNMP agent for this host. If no SNMP agent is configured for this host this will have a value of none.

hostIfTable.name: hostIfTable
hostIfTable.description: Information about the network interfaces on a host.

hostIfEntry.name: hostIfEntry
hostIfEntry.description: This table contains a row for each network interface associated with a host. It is indexed by the canonical IP address of the host and the specific IP address of the interface.

hostIfAddr.name: hostIfAddr
hostIfAddr.description: The specific IP address of the network interface in this row of the table.

hostIfShared.name: hostIfShared
hostIfShared.description: Whether the interface is the shared IP address of the host.

hostIfStatus.name: hostIfStatus
hostIfStatus.description: The status of the network interface.

hostIfTXPackets.name: hostIfTXPackets
hostIfTXPackets.description: The number of packets that have been transmitted on the network interface.

hostIfRXPackets.name: hostIfRXPackets
hostIfRXPackets.description: The number of packets that have been received on the network interface.

hostIfUpTime.name: hostIfUpTime
hostIfUpTime.description: The amount of time the interface has been up.

hostIfAliveTime.name: hostIfAliveTime
hostIfAliveTime.description: The most recent date and time when the interface was known to be running.

hostIfDataTime.name: hostIfDataTime
hostIfDataTime.description: The most recent date and time when data was transmitted through the interface.

hostIfPathSentTime.name: hostIfPathSentTime
hostIfPathSentTime.description: The date and time when path data corresponding to the interface was most recently sent.

hostIfPathsSent.name: hostIfPathsSent
hostIfPathsSent.description: The number of paths sent in the most recent batch.

hostIfPathsRcvd.name: hostIfPathsRcvd
hostIfPathsRcvd.description: The number of paths received in the most recent batch.

hostIfPathSends.name: hostIfPathSends
hostIfPathSends.description: The number of batches of paths that have been sent.

hostIfPathRcvs.name: hostIfPathRcvs
hostIfPathRcvs.description: The number of batches of paths that have been received.

hostIfAvgPathsSentX1000.name: hostIfAvgPathsSentX1000
hostIfAvgPathsSentX1000.description: The average sent path batch size, multiplied by 1000.

hostIfAvgPathsRcvdX1000.name: hostIfAvgPathsRcvdX1000
hostIfAvgPathsRcvdX1000.description: The average received path batch size, multiplied by 1000.

hostIfFctryTable.name: hostIfFctryTable
hostIfFctryTable.description: Information about the factories running on each host interface.

hostIfFctryEntry.name: hostIfFctryEntry
hostIfFctryEntry.description: This table gives the number of factories of each type that are running on each host interface.

hostIfFctryType.name: hostIfFctryType
hostIfFctryType.description: The type of the factory in this row of the table.

hostIfFctryCount.name: hostIfFctryCount
hostIfFctryCount.description: The number of factories of the type corresponding to this row of the table.

hostVServTable.name: hostVServTable
hostVServTable.description: Information about the virtual servers associated with each host.

hostVServEntry.name: hostVServEntry
hostVServEntry.description: This table contains a row for each virtual server on each host other than load-balancing routers. It is indexed by the host address and by the address/port combination that defines the virtual server.

hostVServAddr.name: hostVServAddr
hostVServAddr.description: The IP address of the virtual server.

hostVServPort.name: hostVServPort
hostVServPort.description: The port number of the virtual server.

hostVServXlatedAddr.name: hostVServXlatedAddr
hostVServXlatedAddr.description: The translated (NAT) address of the virtual server.

hostVServXlatedPort.name: hostVServXlatedPort
hostVServXlatedPort.description: The translated (NAT) port number of the virtual server.

hostVServProbeProtocol.name: hostVServProbeProtocol
hostVServProbeProtocol.description: The probing protocol used for measuring round-trip times to the virtual server.

hostVServPicks.name: hostVServPicks
hostVServPicks.description: The number of times the specified virtual server has been chosen by the load-balancing DNS server.

hostVServRefreshes.name: hostVServRefreshes
hostVServRefreshes.description: The number of times that data associated with the virtual server have been refreshed with new information.

hostVServAliveTime.name: hostVServAliveTime
hostVServAliveTime.description: When the virtual server was last known to be up.

hostVServDataTime.name: hostVServDataTime
hostVServDataTime.description: When data was last received from the virtual server.

hostVServDisabled.name: hostVServDisabled
hostVServDisabled.description: Is this virtual server disabled. If a virtual server is disabled it is considered unavailable for load balancing by 3DNS.

hostVServDisableDuration.name: hostVServDisableDuration
hostVServDisableDuration.description: Disable duration of this virtual server.

lbDnsServTable.name: lbDnsServTable
lbDnsServTable.description: Information about the load-balancing DNS servers.

lbDnsServEntry.name: lbDnsServEntry
lbDnsServEntry.description: This table contains a row for each load-balancing DNS server, indexed by the server's canonical IP address.

lbDnsServAddr.name: lbDnsServAddr
lbDnsServAddr.description: The canonical IP address of the load-balancing DNS server.

lbDnsServName.name: lbDnsServName
lbDnsServName.description: The name of the load-balancing DNS server.

lbDnsServProber.name: lbDnsServProber
lbDnsServProber.description: The IP address of the server's prober.

lbDnsServProbeProtocol.name: lbDnsServProbeProtocol
lbDnsServProbeProtocol.description: The The probing protocol used for measuring round-trip times to the server.

lbDnsServProbePort.name: lbDnsServProbePort
lbDnsServProbePort.description: The port to which probes are directed.

lbDnsServStatus.name: lbDnsServStatus
lbDnsServStatus.description: The current status of the server.

lbDnsServPicks.name: lbDnsServPicks
lbDnsServPicks.description: The number of times the host has been chosen.

lbDnsServRefreshes.name: lbDnsServRefreshes
lbDnsServRefreshes.description: The number of times the data from the server has been refreshed with new information.
